==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Persulphocyanogen
<hw>Per*sul`pho*cy*an"o*gen</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>An orange-yellow substance, produced by the
action of chlorine or boiling dilute nitric acid and sulphocyanate of
potassium; -- called also <altname>pseudosulphocyanogen</altname>,
<altname>perthiocyanogen</altname>, and formerly
<altname>sulphocyanogen</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Persulphuret</ent>⟦br⟧
